  "texts": [
    "Performing the integral over α *, this simplifies to:",
    "This resulting expression is a convolution of the microlens deflection probability density with the background magnification model.",
    "What was once a point source has, on average, been \"smeared out\" into a source with a profile that looks like p(α *).",
    "The form of the probability density function of α * was first worked out by Katz et al. (1986), while Schneider et al. (1992) provide it in a slightly different form and Petters et al. (2009a) present a more thorough mathematical treatment.",
    "This function is isotropic and depends only on the magnitude of the deflection angle, not the direction."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The form of the probability density function of α * was first worked out by Katz et al. (1986), while Schneider et al. (1992) provide it in a slightly different form and Petters et al. (2009a) present a more thorough mathematical treatment."
  ]
